    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "A travel agency offers three vacation packages. Each package has a fixed number of days and a fixed daily price. The agency wants to show the total price for each package. All three packages use the same daily price.\r\n\r\n✅ **TO DO #1:** In <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">TravelAgency.java</code>, declare and initialize a constant called <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">DAILY\\_RATE</code> to <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">250</code>.\r\n\r\n✅ **TO DO #2:** Update each total price calculation to use the constant instead of repeating the number <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">250</code>.\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background-color: #E0D1EC; border: 1px solid #9660bf; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 1.1em; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 10px;\">\r\n💡 <strong>TIP:</strong> Check out the <strong>Help & Tips</strong> tab ⬆️ for help with declaring and initializing a constant.\r\n</div>",
